##CSS-Cascading Style Sheets(CSS)
->CSS was first proposed by Hakon Wium Lie on October 10,1994.

Q.What is CSS?
->Cascading Style Sheets(CSS) is a style sheet language used for describing the presentation of a document written in a markup language.  

#Characteristics of CSS
1.Allows computing devices to display web pages differently.
2.Enables the separation of presentation and content.
3.Improves content accessibility.
4.Uses selectors in order to target HTML elements.
5.Declaration blocks are used to specify changes.

#Defining a CSS declaration block
h1 {
   color:blue;
   font-size:12px;
 }

h1->selector

{ }->declaration block 

color->attribute
blue-> value

font-size->attribute
12px->value

#Common Selectors
1) .class
Example: .container
Details: Selects all elements with a class name of container

2) #id
Example: #student-number
Details: Selects an element with a uniquely identifiable ID i.e student number

3) element
Example: h1
Details: Selects all <h1> elements

4) element, element
Example: div, p
Details: Selects all <div> elements and all <p> elements

5) element element
Example: nav li
Details: Selects all <li> elements inside <nav> elements

6) element + element
Example: div + h2
Details: Selects all <h2> elements that are placed immediately after <div> elements